content.value: Public Overridable ReadOnly Property UniqueID As String

children.remarks: The unique identifier for a test case should be able to discriminate among test cases, even those which are varied invocations against the same test method (i.e., theories). This identifier should remain stable until such time as the developer changes some fundamental part of the identity (assembly, class name, test name, or test data). Recompilation of the test assembly is reasonable as a stability changing event.
